Given a string consisting of lowercase English letters, you can change one character to another in each round. This function calculates the minimum number of rounds needed to make the string composed of the same character.
@param {string} s - The input string.
@returns {number} The minimum number of rounds to make all characters in the string the same.

canonical_solution:
function minRoundsToSameChar(s)
{
    const charCount = new Array(26).fill(0); // Assuming only lowercase letters
    for (const char of s) {
        charCount[char.charCodeAt(0) - 'a'.charCodeAt(0)]++;
    }
    let maxCount = 0;
    for (const count of charCount) {
        if (count !== 0) {
            maxCount++;
        }
    }

    return maxCount - 1;
}

